<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id474c59b6-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s7410"><num value="7410">§ 7410.</num><heading> Cross references</heading><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I23" class="indent2 fontsize7" id="id474c59b7-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s7410/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> For provisions for collecting taxes in general, see chapter 64.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I23" class="indent2 fontsize7" id="id474c59b8-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s7410/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> For venue in a civil action for the collection of any tax, see <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s1396">section 1396 of Title 28</ref> of the United States Code.</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I23" class="indent2 fontsize7" id="id474c59b9-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a" identifier="/us/usc/t26/s7410/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> For venue of a proceeding for the recovery of any fine, penalty, or forfeiture, see <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s1395">section 1395 of Title 28</ref> of the United States Code.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id474c59ba-3a70-11f1-a967-d35dac11796a">(<ref href="/us/act/1954-08-16/ch736">Aug. 16, 1954, ch. 736</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/68A/875">68A Stat. 875</ref>, § 7407; renumbered § 7408, <ref href="/us/pl/94/455/tXII/s1203/g">Pub. L. 94–455, title XII, § 1203(g)</ref>, <date date="1976-10-04">Oct. 4, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/1693">90 Stat. 1693</ref>; renumbered § 7409, <ref href="/us/pl/97/248/tIII/s321/a">Pub. L. 97–248, title III, § 321(a)</ref>, <date date="1982-09-03">Sept. 3, 1982</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/96/612">96 Stat. 612</ref>; renumbered § 7410, <ref href="/us/pl/100/203/tX/s10713/a/1">Pub. L. 100–203, title X, § 10713(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="1987-12-22">Dec. 22, 1987</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/101/1330-468">101 Stat. 1330–468</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
